"{\"uid\": \"www.huffingtonpost.co.uk.-entry-credit-suisse-ceo-tidjane-thiam-blames-brexit-on-britains-lack-of-investment-in-education-uk-\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The chief executive of Credit Suisse has laid the blame for the Brexit vote at the feet of Britain's \\\"chronic lack of investment in education\\\".\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23, \"end\": 36, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Credit_Suisse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Credit Suisse\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Credit_Suisse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Credit_Suisse\"}, {\"begin\": 64, \"end\": 70, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brexit\", \"score\": 0.9999957621736241, \"rank\": 4.2378443588940844e-06, \"text\": \"Brexit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brexit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brexit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tidjane Thiam was remarking on the country's decision to leave the European Union as voted for by a majority of 52%, during a business conference in France.\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 145, \"end\": 158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tidjane_Thiam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tidjane Thiam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tidjane_Thiam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tidjane_Thiam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thiam also said he was shocked at the high levels of inequality in the country, particularly after visiting a school in Tower Hamlets, where he was told around half the pupils only ate once a day.\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  CEO Tidjane Thiam of Swiss bank Credit Suisse Arnd Wiegmann / Reuters  \\\"That's something I had seen in the Ivory Coast,\\\" Thiam, who is a former government minister in the West African country, told Reuters.\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The banker believes the solution lies in a more redistributive tax system - even if that meant raising taxes - to ensure those who have lost out to globalization are not left feeling disenfranchised.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thiam, who took over the bank last summer, says he watched and backed the anti-Brexit march in London on Saturday, but added: \\\"I would have liked to say to them: 'how many more of you would accept to pay more taxes?'\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  \\\"It's all well and good to have big signs and protest against the 'Leave' vote.\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it would be another story if you started having a discussion about creating more solidarity.\\\"\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He added that those with the lowest levels of education were most likely to back Brexit, summing up: \\\"That's the price paid for a chronic lack of investment in education.\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Something must be done at the national level so there are not so many people left behind that the result of a national, democratic vote gives a result which is bad for the country in the medium term.\\\"\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Years of austerity coupled with mass immigration have kindled resentment, particularly among the white working class, against elites in London - and by extension the EU's headquarters in Brussels seen as responsible for an influx of Europeans to Britain.\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a growing income gap, a Credit Suisse report found that the number of million-dollar-wealth households rose 30 percent between 2013 and 2014 alone.\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 2123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  The outcome was also a sombre reminder that the capital, where votes were strongly skewed toward remain, is at odds with much of the rest of the country.\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The city's economy, strongly linked to international trade and banking, is now expected to take a hit as markets face years of uncertainty over Britain's ties with Europe.\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2466, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In February Thiam proposed that its board make a \\\"significant\\\" cut to his bonus after the Swiss bank posted disappointing earnings and announced 4,000 job cuts.\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2628, \"entities\": []}]}"